reviews.review: The movie is really well done. I think people love to hate and that’s what the critics are doing to this one.

It's not fan service, it's producer service done poorly and denying the whole of "Last Jedi"'s major innovations. 
-SPOILERS- 
Rey's origin is revealed, and it's as poorly constructed and purposeful as Palpatine's introduction (WHICH IS DONE AT THE TITLE WITHOUT ANY EXPLANATION!!)
J.J. Abrams doesn't know how to end stuff well, but is going to make a lot of money anyway. It's up to you to help him with that by buying tickets to an empty film with an awful plot and off-the-charts corny dialogue.
was exciting, love and crying involved. Was a great movie!
Great movie, if you're a 12 year old and coherent plots don't matter much. At that age you're more concerned with the SFX, which this film has plenty of.

I really enjoyed this final installment. I’m sad to think of what it could have been had TLJ been a worthy installment, but JJ did a good job of redeeming the series and bringing about a fun and meaningful end to the series. I also enjoyed the ways in which Rey and Finn developed as characters.

It wasn't bad, but wasn't that great either. It was more of a fetch quest without any lasting consequences... chewbacca died (nope), Kylo Ren died (nope), C3PO had his memory wiped (nope). The only way to defeat Palestine is becoming new embodiment of the sith (nope). 

In short the movie attempts to give the shock factor without dealing with any consequences. It was a fan-servicey fetch quest that doesn't follow a classic 3 part structure. It was meh at best
If you liked tLJ you will hate this movie. If you hated tLJ, like most people, you will probably like this movie. I thought it was a lot of fun. People take Star Wars too seriously.
A satisfying conclusion and the best we could’ve asked for in light of a laundry list of particular circumstances.

The movie was amazing! Couldn't have concluded the saga any better. I don't know where all the hate came from? Well done J. J. & company. The characters were never more likable than in this episode. Time to book some tickets for viewing number two.
